RESOLVED_ENTITIES.the route: U.S. Highway 59 and Farm-to-Market Road 2050 and U.S. Highway 359

AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.U.S. Highway 59: a highway where Agent Trevino was inspecting vehicles, near the Freer immigration checkpoint, intersecting with Farm-to-Market Road 2050 to the west of Freer immigration checkpoint, used to avoid checkpoints, has a checkpoint that vehicles pass through, location of a traffic stop, route Agent Benavides drove to
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Farm-to-Market Road 2050: a road with limited traffic, mostly used by local residents and workers, such as ranchers, oilfield trucks, and utility trucks, adjacent to the Border Patrol station parking lot, connected to U.S. 59, where vehicles drop off illegal aliens between the Freer immigration checkpoint and Bruni, and a point where aliens walk east to Highway 16, part of a route avoiding checkpoints via FM 2050, U.S. 59, and U.S. 359
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Highway 16: route where picked-up aliens are taken after walking from Farm-to-Market Road 2050, allowing access to Houston or San Antonio to the north, provides vehicle access from San Pablo Road and Santo Nino Road, road where Officer Reymundo Reyes noticed a vehicle, route taken towards San Antonio, route Agent Benavides drove to, mentioned as a reference point for an intersection
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.U.S. Highway 359: road intersecting with Farm-to-Market Road 2050 to the east of the Hebbronville checkpoint, used to avoid checkpoints, one of the roads connected by Farm-to-Market Road 2050
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.U.S. Highway 59 and Farm-to-Market Road: routes used to avoid checkpoints via FM 2050, U.S. 59, and U.S. 359
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Highway 35: the most direct route to Dallas, Texas or San Antonio
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Mills Bennett Road: a dirt road intersecting Farm-to-Market Road 2050, approximately five miles south of the Freer immigration checkpoint
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.San Pablo Road: a road south of the wind farm, extending to the east off Farm-to-Market Road 2050, provides vehicle access to Highway 16, nearby location to where the stop was initiated
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Santo Nino Road: also known as Dinn Ranch, extends to the east and provides vehicle access to Highway 16
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Interstate 35: the best route from Laredo, Texas to Dallas, Texas
